Types
HandChirality
public enum HandChirality
LEFT

The left hand

RIGHT

The right hand

HandType
public enum HandType
PRIMARY

The first hand found

SECONDARY

The second hand found

InputType
public enum InputType
NONE

Used to be ignored by the input system but to still receive information such as distance to screen

CANCEL

Used to cancel the current input if an issue occurs. Particularly when a DOWN has happened before an UP

DOWN

Used to begin a 'Touch' or a 'Drag'

MOVE

Used to move a cursor or to perform a 'Drag' after a DOWN

UP

Used to complete a 'Touch' or a 'Drag'

InteractionType
public enum InteractionType
GRAB

The user must perform a GRAB gesture to 'Touch' by bringing their fingers and thumb together

HOVER

The user must perform a HOVER gesture to 'Touch' by holding their hand still for a fixed time

PUSH

The user must perform a PUSH gesture to 'Touch' by pushing their hand toward the screen

BitmaskFlags
[Flags]
public enum BitmaskFlags

This is used to request any combination of the HandChiralities, HandTypes, InputTypes, and InteractionTypes flags from the Service at once.

WebsocketInputAction

public struct
Ultraleap.​TouchFree.​Tooling.​WebsocketInputAction

The version of an InputAction received via the WebSocket. This must be converted into a InputAction to be used by the Tooling and can be done so via its constructor.
